## Interactive Exercises
- **Mini-quiz**: 2-3 multiple choice after each video, instant feedback
- **Chat Simulator**: Simulates Infloww-like interface. Fan messages → choose action → feedback. THE killer feature.
- **Scenario Cards**: Situation → click to reveal → correct answer

## Video Production Design System
- Background: warm paper tone (#f7f3eb) with grid lines, NOT white/blue
- Minimum 2 visual elements per scene
- 10 component types: ComparisonPanel, FlowDiagram, StepProgression, ChatMockup, StatHighlight, IconGrid, QuoteMantra, Checklist, HierarchyTree, NumberCircle
- 5 layouts: split, stack, grid-2x2, hero-center, timeline
- Automated QA pre-render: validates visual elements, duration, terms defined, example present

## Interview Structure (Updated)
- Removed: formal intro, logistics check, English assessment
- Kept: "Tell me about yourself" (3 min), Motivation Check (3 min), Knowledge Check (7 min), Quick Writing Test (2 min)
- Pass: motivated, knowledge correct, B1+ English + personality in writing
- Fail: can't answer basics, poor English, unclear motivation, red flags

## Key Teaching Concepts
- Script commands use `/` (forward slash), NOT `\`
- "Unread" tab is Step 0 of every shift checklist
- Before each training group: verify training model has ALL current scripts
- Annotated Chat Examples: sourced from real Infloww conversations, prepared by senior TL (one-time task)
